  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What is the deal with CotH???</span><hr size=1> With all of the nerfing and such that goes on it is sometimes hard for me to keep up with what a spell actually does lol...Does CotH still have an agro removal component?  If so are there any restrictions to its use?  Any info would be greatly appreciated.  thank you in advance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadissadevion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adissa DeVion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 6:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1519.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is the deal with CotH???</span><hr size=1> CoH still clears aggro if the distance between you and the group member you summoned is far enough. There is a limit for CoH and a group member can be oor for the spell indeed, I think the range is about 1000 feet or something, didnt happen to me so far so im not sure about the exact range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxurtsdunnit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xurts Dunnit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 6:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1519.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is the deal with CotH???</span><hr size=1> Originally CotH would strip any agro from the callee.<br>
CotH was change in that it would only strip the agro from the callee if the callee was a certain distance or greater from the caller.  If that distance is not great enough, the callee remains on the hate list, and the NPC behaves according to it's AI (which would probably add the caller to the hate list as well, since CotH would be considered a beneficial spell, much like a heal). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwoonx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 6:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1519.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is the deal with CotH???</span><hr size=1> Actualy the range between you and the person you CoH doesn't matter, it's the range between CoH spot and the mob that the person is aggro on. You can clear aggro of someone at your feet if the mobs is far from you. On the other hand you can kill him if you summon him in range of that same mob. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</A>&nbsp<A href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&ltTDE&gt</A><BR>
Arch mage, 7th hammer<BR>
<A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112180">Krisgor</A>&nbsp53 SK<BR>
<A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112210">Khrana</A>&nbsp50 Shamanette of doom<BR>
 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucelanxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CelanXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 8:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1519.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> There is a max range for CoH too. While summoning people to Fay's cove in TD, people had to be on ogre island before they could be summoned (if they were farther north or on the boat soon after zone in, the distance was too great). So it's like 15k loc points or something like that for the max range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujayteebushwacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 977<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 8:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1519.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is the deal with CotH???</span><hr size=1> Moved to the Spells section. <p><hr>
