<br>
I did two small tests.  I sent a shadowknight in to aggro a couple mobs in ssra, atttacking only the farthest one, I stood about 110-120 ft away.  I summoned her. Her aggro cleared completely.<br>
<br>
I then went out into the grey, and agrod a skeleton.  I then ran far far far away, CoHd myself, then came back and the skeleton still had aggro on me.<br>
<br>
CoH has not changed, and ever since the Conquest incident, it has always required you be 100 ft away from the person you are summoning.<br>
<br>
I will tell you what does seem to have changed though.  Seemingly after last patch...if you cast a spell at nighttime while standing infront of a halfling, and the spell hits exactly when an EQ hour hits, you are never resisted. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
